FEATURES             Location/Qualifiers
     protein_domain  1..16
                     /label="SpyTag003"
                     /synonym="SpyTag 003"
                     /synonym="SpyTag003"
                     /note="16-aa third-generation Spy peptide tag
                     (RGVPHIVMVDAYKRYK). Engineered from SpyTag002 by appending
                     an N-terminal Arg-Gly (RG) dipeptide and introducing the
                     T112H mutation (CnaB2 numbering), descended from the CnaB2
                     domain of Streptococcus pyogenes FbaB. On mixing with its
                     116-aa partner SpyCatcher003 it forms a spontaneous,
                     irreversible intermolecular isopeptide (amide) bond between
                     its reactive Asp (CnaB2 Asp117) and Lys31 of SpyCatcher003,
                     catalysed by SpyCatcher Glu77 - reaction approaches the
                     diffusion limit. Fusable at N-terminus, C-terminus or
                     internally. Contains no Cys."
                     /citation=[1]
